$Id$
Updated for Hybrid 6.4 (2003/11/26)

When you type /version you will often see something like this:
2.8/hybrid-6.4 (20030701_1). irc.ircd-hybrid.org AeGiKMpZ TS5ow

Ever wondered what those funny chars mean after the version number? Well
here they are:

'A'	SENDQ_ALWAYS
'C'	CMDLINE_CONFIG
'D'	DEBUGMODE
'e'	CHANMODE_E
'g'	NO_FAKE_GLINES
'G'	GLINES
'H'	HUB
'i'	SHOW_INVISIBLE_LUSERS
'I'	CHANMODE_I
'K'	USE_KNOCK
'M'	IDLE_FROM_MSG
'p'	CRYPT_OPER_PASSWORD
'P'	CRYPT_LINK_PASSWORD
'r'     LITTLE_I_LINES (restricted mode)
'S'	OPERSPY
'T'     IGNORE_BOGUS_TS
'Y'	USE_SYSLOG
'Z'	ZIP_LINKS

'TS'    Supports TS
'3'     TS Version 3 (Gives ops on splits, on opless channels)
'5'	TS Version 5 (Impossible to gain ops after a netsplit)
'o'     TS Only
'w'     TS Warnings
'c'	TS Current and higher only.
